            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <head>288. Telegram From the Embassy in Iran to the Department of State<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d288fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss> 84, Tehran Embassy Files, Lot 60 F 86,
                        general records, 1953–1955, Box 7. Restricted; <gloss target="#t_NIACT_1"
                            >NIACT</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CA_1">Cuomo</persName>
                        and repeated <gloss target="#t_NIACT_1">NIACT</gloss> to London. The
                        telegram is the Embassy copy as approved and has no time of
                        transmission.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Tehran</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-19"
                        >August 19, 1953</date>.</dateline>
                <p>400. PTT and Press and Propaganda offices occupied. Telegrams reportedly being
                    sent provinces urging pro-Shah action similar that of Tehran.</p>
                <p>Embassy officers report truckloads soldiers, civilians and six tanks seen roaming
                    city displaying pictures Shah.</p>
                <p>Radio Tehran played nothing but recorded music for short period after Press and
                    Propaganda taken and silent thereafter.</p>
                <p>General <persName corresp="#p_DG_1">Daftari</persName> reportedly appointed
                    Tehran Military Governor and Police Chief. He apparently attempting use,
                    according Embassy radio intercepts, Customs Guards organization he previously
                    commanded in behalf <persName corresp="#p_MM_1">Mosadeq</persName> regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_HLW_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HLW_1">Henderson</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
